node.text:
Pet dog, pat cat or pet giraffes? 🦒Hanging out with friendly giants in Nairobi, a destination known for its beautiful national parks and diverse wildlife. 😍

Set in the Langata suburb of Nairobi and shot in Giraffe Manor, this incredible footage shows the inquisitive nature of these beautiful and gentle giants. Giraffes live primarily in savanna areas in the sub-Saharan region of Africa and are known to be friendly and social animals by nature.🦒

What’s your favourite safari animal?

🎥 @_khloe.g 
Vid 2 @venelin_k & @inagallardo_adamand

Which of these helicopter rides would you choose? 🚁
1. Sunset Cruise
2. River Rip
3. Van City Experience

With your one of a kind guide @mrbentley_thedog 🐶 & pilot @bradleyfriesen 👨🏻‍✈️

🎥 Vid 1 - @devinolsen 
Vid 2 & 3 - @emmett_sparling 

Does your pet join in on your adventures, too? Tag who you’d take on this 🚁 ride!

📍Canada

node.text:
Who says mermaids don’t exist!? 🥰 I bet the manatee was just as surprised as @shellseaflmermaid 🧜‍♀️ 

Besides the pristine water and swarm of fish in this natural Florida spring, the manatee's surprise appearance makes this footage even more incredible. 🇺🇸 Great shot @themikerioux 🙌

Manatees are curious by nature and often initiate interaction with humans; so if you happen to see manatees while swimming, snorkeling, diving, or boating, it's important to avoid doing anything disruptive. You can "look but don't touch" while practicing passive observation from a distance, avoid excessive noise and splashing, and resist the urge to feed them. (source: savethemanatee.org) ✔️

Have you ever seen a manatee before? 😍

🎥 @themikerioux
🧜‍♀️ @shellseaflmermaid
📍 Florida, US
🎶 Kathleen - Pure Imagination
